oogle 的订阅和服务，但据报道其替代文字是：“一个人用 Porcelain 的 Pixel 8 Pro 手机接听电话。” </p><div id="97d09bca91014fdd8688e284a8dae7df"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">这是瓷质 Google Pixel 8 Pro 的外观。<br><br>此图片来自 Google 商店网站，该网站无意中在“Google 订阅和服务”的促销页面早期发布了此图片。<br><br>感谢<a href="https://twitter.com/android_setting?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@android_setting</a>的提示！ <a href="https://t.co/nARd4Hz8hk">pic.twitter.com/nARd4Hz8hk</a></p> — 米沙尔·拉赫曼 (@MishaalRahman) <a href="https://twitter.com/MishaalRahman/status/1696728025310597312?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 8 月 30 日</a></blockquote></div><p>图像中的设备类似于<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-pixel-8-pro-prototype-revealed-in-leak-091118014.html">之前泄露的模型原型照片</a>中的手机。它的后置摄像头位于一块玻璃面板内，该玻璃面板内有一根横跨手机整个宽度的凸起金属条。当然，谷歌的“G”标志位于设备的中心。根据之前的其他泄露（是的，有很多），Pixel 8 Pro 的摄像头阵列由一个 50 兆像素的主摄像头（可让光线增加 50%）和一个 64 兆像素的超宽索尼摄像头组成。还有传言称它采用<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-pixel-8-pro-could-feature-a-flat-display-200049745.html">平面显示屏</a>，而不是类似于 Pixel 6 Pro 和 Pixel 7 Pro 的曲面显示屏。此外，预计还将配备 5,000 mAh 电池和 27W 最大充电速度。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>谷歌的 Pixel 8 Pro 尚未确定发布日期，但这家科技巨头在<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-6-and-6-pro-hands-on-tensor-features-camera-specs-available-price-170038272.html">2021 年</a>10 月和<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7-pixel-7-pro-pixel-watch-event-wrap-up-170055623.html">2022 年</a>举行的一次活动中推出了前两代产品。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/google-totally-didnt-mean-to-leak-the-pixel-8-pro-on-its-own-website-101528033.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-totally-didnt-mean-to-leak-the-pixel-8-pro-on-its-own-website-101528033.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9f43af73-9dc1-4b84-8388-385ce29046a6</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 30 Aug 2023 10:15:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693393274</ingested><modified> 2023-08-30T11:01:27+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="806" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7e1d0ef0-470b-11ee-8ed3-a0ef6f638819" width="1195"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="806" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7e1d0ef0-470b-11ee-8ed3-a0ef6f638819" width="1195"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Google]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A man wearing a pink beanie and a blue blazer holding a porcelain-colored smartphone against his ear.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google Pixel 8 Pro]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Fairphone 5 is boring… how exciting!]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>智能手机世界的前沿真正令人兴奋已经有很多年了。业界可能希望我们对其最新的 5G、108 兆像素折叠屏杰作垂涎欲滴，但我仍然口干舌燥。对我来说，这是因为在过去的四五年里，可能性的上限并没有上升太多，但底部却一直在缓慢地向北蠕动。从纸面上看，刚刚发布的 Fairphone 5 具有您所期望的中端手机的规格。但现在这并不是真正的惩罚，因为你还获得了一款模块化、可持续制造且可能可升级的手机，这些手机是由支付公平工资的人们制造的。和其他智能手机一样，它只是一部智能手机。一方面，这让新的 Fairphone 5 变得无聊，但从这个角度来看，<em>无聊也可能是件好事</em>。</p><p> Fairphone 的使命是打造“ <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-02-06-ethical-smartphone-conscious-consumption.html">更好</a>”的智能手机，十年后，尚不清楚 Fairphone 是否还需要全面介绍。对于不知情的人来说，荷兰社会企业生产的设备比竞争对手“更公平”。这意味着向工厂工人支付生活工资、采购“道德”原材料、使用回收材料并尽可能长时间地避免硬件被扔进垃圾箱。为此，每个设备都是模块化的，易于维修，有时可以升级，而且通常比竞争对手更耐用。它不像谷歌长期哀悼的 Project Ara 那样奇特，但它比想象中的模块化、可升级手机的梦想更真实。在这里，拿起飞利浦 00 头螺丝刀并在几分钟内安装新组件<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fairphone-3-3-plus-repair-camera-swap-153053319.html">不仅是可能的，而且是简单的</a>。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Fairphone 5 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fairphone-4-5g-preview-103011717.html">在尺寸和风格上与前代产品的</a>模板相差不远。它具有相同的带有天线交叉的厚重底盘、相同的相机外壳、相同的指纹感应电源按钮和相同的易于拆卸的背板。与 2023 年发布的许多手机一样，这些变化也反映了行业的现状。因此，现在的电池容量更大了，显示屏更大了，相机的功能也比上一代更强大了。 Fairphone 还可以单独更换每个摄像头，从而使维修或升级摄像头变得更容易、更便宜。</p><p>您将能够获得大量备件，只有主机架无法单独购买。产品清单包括 90Hz、6.46 英寸 LG 制造的 POLED 显示屏、4,200mAh 电池和所有三个摄像头。您还可以获得备用耳机、扬声器、USB-C 端口和包含飞行时间传感器的顶部装置，以及 SIM 和 SD 卡插槽。如果这款手机的某个部件坏了，您将能够以不多的现金买到几乎所有您需要的东西。最贵的组件是显示屏，售价为 99.95 欧元（约合 108 美元），大约是<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvc3VwcG9ydC9jcmFja2VkLXNjcmVlbi1yZXBhaXIvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4YTcyYTQ0Zi0zZGQxLTQ3ODMtYTg2MS03OTgzMDVmOGFlZWIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAQxhLnL712UBLzu1MLY7vs17j7pZT0mEyNUb4DL4EZSE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Fsupport%2Fcracked-screen-repair%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.samsung.com/us/support/cracked-screen-repair/">三星售价</a>的一半，几乎是<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N1cHBvcnQuYXBwbGUuY29tL2lwaG9uZS9yZXBhaXIvc2NyZWVuLXJlcGxhY2VtZW50IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4YTcyYTQ0Zi0zZGQxLTQ3ODMtYTg2MS03OTgzMDVmOGFlZWIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXMZqZGsRAajEbe6y30FViHlNmI-35FrQoJBg2yiEKQY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fiphone%2Frepair%2Fscreen-replacement" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://support.apple.com/iphone/repair/screen-replacement">苹果要价</a>的三分之一。</p><p>为了兑现其可持续性和使用寿命的承诺，Fairphone 5 采用了高通八核<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.qualcomm.com/products/internet-of-things/industrial/building-enterprise/qcm6490">QCM6490 SoC</a> 。据我所知，这是一款工业级物联网芯片组，仅在另一款手机中使用：AGM 配备热成像摄像头的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hZ21tb2JpbGUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2FnbS1nMi1ndWFyZGlhbiIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGE3MmE0NGYtM2RkMS00NzgzLWE4NjEtNzk4MzA1ZjhhZWViIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAbk2Es5zpzCByksAz2hM-aR3bWxPcY_-Y1D6w08mUrn7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.agmmobile.com%2Fproducts%2Fagm-g2-guardian" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.agmmobile.com/products/agm-g2-guardian">G2 Guardian</a> 。这里只有一个 SKU，Fairphone 5 配备 8GB RAM 和非常大的 256GB 存储空间，可通过合适的 microSD 卡扩展至 2TB。 Fairphone 表示，这一选择是由该芯片组融合了 6G、WiFi 6E 和片上 AI 处理等高级功能决定的。更不用说高通承诺支持其工业级芯片的时间比其移动芯片的支持时间还要长。为此，Fairphone 承诺支持（几乎）Android 13 的原生安装以及“之后至少五次操作系统升级”。 （考虑到 Android 14 即将发布，你应该预计它会在不久的将来出现在你的手机上。）该公司表示，预计至少会在 2028 年之前提供软件支持，但希望能够一直运行到 2033 年。</p><p> Fairphone 现在已经建立了能够让其手机运行相当长一段时间的记录。 Fairphone 2 于 2015 年推出，搭载 Android 5.1，并于 2023 年 3 月通过 Android 10 更新获得最终安全补丁。七年左右的软件支持是转换的一个很好的理由，特别是当三星承诺为“精选”手机提供<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL25ld3Muc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvc2Ftc3VuZy1nYWxheHktb3MtdXBncmFkZS1vbmUtdWktYW5kcm9pZC11bnBhY2tlZC0yMDIyLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGE3MmE0NGYtM2RkMS00NzgzLWE4NjEtNzk4MzA1ZjhhZWViIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAc5p0vDShCNXt_DATypsnxDqMNcgzOKoJZpDMIEaPP_O&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.samsung.com%2Fus%2Fsamsung-galaxy-os-upgrade-one-ui-android-unpacked-2022%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://news.samsung.com/us/samsung-galaxy-os-upgrade-one-ui-android-unpacked-2022/">四年的软件</a>和五年的<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://security.samsungmobile.com/securityPost.smsb">安全更新</a>时。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/9d7ad830-466c-11ee-9e9f-5f324ff6b360" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/9d7ad830-466c-11ee-9e9f-5f324ff6b360" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Fairphone 5 的图片，后盖和电池在螺丝刀上方打开。" data-uuid="a0020430-661e-302c-b61d-a135d4e39be2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">丹尼尔·库珀 / Engadget 摄</div></figure><p>在我试用新型号的有限时间内，我发现它的性能比旧款 Fairphone 快很多。操作系统本身的动画和过渡在早期阶段并没有出现延迟，Epic 模式下的<em>《堡垒之夜》</em>以 30 fps 的速度完美运行。我当然注意到，与上一部手机相比，使用我的面部和指纹解锁这款手机的速度要快得多。乍一看，这似乎完全能够满足您对正常手机使用的期望。好吧，如果你认为手机的正常使用是发短信、电子邮件、社交媒体、YouTube、TikTok 和奇怪的死亡竞赛。</p><p>我认为 Fairphone 5 的成像是可靠的，尽管我担心这样做会是对它的微弱赞扬。由索尼 IMX800 传感器支持的 50 兆像素、f/1.88、配备 OIS 的主摄像头足以满足大多数人的摄影需求。它可能不具备同类设备中某些设备的软件智能，但它并不逊色，尤其是在视频方面。看一眼 Fairphone 5 的背面，你会发现一个与相机镜头大小相同的圆圈，这就是 ToF 传感器。这是这款手机的秘密武器，尤其是在拍摄视频时闪电般快速的自动对焦。</p><p>这并不全是好事：在重负载运行时，手机的温度比我想象的要高一些，但这在 5G 时代感觉是正常的。同时，内置扬声器非常小，如果您手头有耳机，我永远不会建议使用它来播放音频。我还认为，在我的借用单元中，纯黑色封面比透明版本的防污能力要好得多。我希望，除了黑色、透明和天蓝色配色外，该公司还提供了<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fairphone-launches-a-fully-repairable-set-of-over-ear-headphones-080017046.html">与 Fairbuds XL 上同样精彩的绿色和橙色涂装</a>。</p><p>遗憾的是，我们还没有看到 Fairphone 5 在美国广泛发布，至少在欧洲没有同时发布。 <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-modular-fairphone-4-arrives-in-the-us-for-the-first-time-155721165.html">Fairphone 4 可在美国购买</a>，其操作系统由专注于隐私的初创公司 Murena 提供。我确信 5 将来也会经历类似的旅程，但很高兴看到同时发布，这样人们就不必等待一年或更长时间才能获得更新的硬件。</p><p>我之前说过，Fairphone 总是带有一种妥协选择的味道，你购买软木和大麻运动鞋是为了减轻你对自己拥有的所有血汗工厂制造的鞋子的负罪感。但是，由于 Fairphone 为改进其产品所做的努力，以及移动行业普遍的停滞，热门产品和不热门产品之间的差距已经缩小了很多。如果您正在寻找一款中档手机，其使用寿命是市场上任何其他手机的两倍，并且您希望在此过程中做一些好事，那么这款手机可能适合您。从道德制高点看到的景色<em>如此</em>令人舒服的情况并不常见。</p><p> Fairphone 5 即日起即 8 月 30 日即可通过该公司网站和多家欧洲主要运营商进行预订。它的售价为 699 欧元（约合 750 美元），预计将于 9 月 14 日开始从 Fairphone 及其大多数运营商发货。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/fairphone-5-is-boring-how-exciting-094530738.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/fairphone-5-is-boring-how-exciting-094530738.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8a72a44f-3dd1-4783-a861-798305f8aeeb</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 30 Aug 2023 09:45:30 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693394727</ingested><modified> 2023-08-30T11:25:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/4369dfb0-4664-11ee-9bbf-421fbd478081" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/4369dfb0-4664-11ee-9bbf-421fbd478081" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Daniel Cooper / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Image of the new Fairphone 5 on a wooden table.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Fairphone 5]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sony's two new A7C series cameras offer premium features for less money]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Sony has just split its small form-factor full-frame <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-a-7-c-review-smart-small-clumsy-153031933.html">A7C series</a> , now offering two lower-cost versions of higher-end cameras — much as it did with the <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonys-12-megapixel-full-frame-zv-e1-is-a-low-light-vlogging-beast-140009036.html">ZV-E1 vlogging camera</a> . The <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://pressroom.pixelshift.studio/sony-electronics-releases-two-new-alpha-7c-series-cameras">new models</a> are the 33-megapixel A7C II (based on the <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-a7-iv-mirrorless-camera-review-163026066.html">A7 IV</a> ), and the 61-megapixel A7C R, a mini-me version <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-a7r-v-review-awesome-images-improved-video-unbeatable-autofocus-150058082.html">of the A7R V</a> . Both are nearly as powerful as the larger versions and offer key ergonomic updates, but lack a few features that pros may find essential.</p><h3> Sony A7C R</h3><p> We&#39;ll start with the A7C R, since it&#39;s an all-new model. It features a softer, grippier material along with a deeper handle. It also comes with an add-on grip that extends the length, giving you a place to put your pinky finger — a nice addition that unfortunately also makes the camera less compact. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/ecfea420-46ff-11ee-bbbe-b7962e70ed52" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/ecfea420-46ff-11ee-bbbe-b7962e70ed52" style="height:1520px;width:2200px;" alt="索尼 A7C 系列推出续集和新 61 兆像素版本" data-uuid="4585f183-cd27-31e8-a53f-b002c35f1150"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sony</div></figure><p> Still, those are key improvements that address ergonomic issues I&#39;ve noticed on past Sony models — particularly when using them for a long day of shooting. Sony also added a front dial so you can more easily adjust aperture/shutter speed/exposure compensation, along with a dedicated video/photo/S&amp;Q dial. And of course, the A7C R weighs just 515 grams (18.2 ounces) compared to the A7R V&#39;s 723 grams (25.5 ounces) and is nearly half the size. That makes it a better choice for street photography and more.</p><p> It has a flip-out one-million dot display and 2.36-million dot OLED electronic viewfinder with slightly improved .70X magnification over the A7C II. It also offers full in-body stabilization with 7.0 stops of compensation (depending on the lens) — a nice feature in such a small camera. Other features include mic/headphone ports, USB-C 3.2, a micro HDMI connector a and single UHS-II card slot. The latter feature is a show-stopper for many pros, as there&#39;s no backup for potentially priceless photos. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/66773ec0-470a-11ee-bf69-cbec03d8c379" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/66773ec0-470a-11ee-bf69-cbec03d8c379" style="height:1467px;width:2200px;" alt="索尼 A7C 系列推出续集和新 61 兆像素版本" data-uuid="32442a19-a9ea-3ce7-8f76-82627435372e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sony</div></figure><p> In terms of photo specs, it&#39;s close to the A7R V with a few notable differences. You can shoot 61-megapixel RAW images at up to 8fps, compared to 10fps on the A7R V. The A7C R has a smaller buffer, though, and that single lower-speed SD UHS-II card slot (the A7R V has dual high-speed CFexpress Type A and SD UHS II slots), so you won&#39;t be able to capture nearly as many photos in a burst. Like the A7R V, the A7C R has 693 autofocus points and 79 percent coverage. It uses the same processor, so should offer roughly the same AF performance in terms of burst shooting, AI tracking and more.</p><p> Most importantly, you can expect identical image quality to the A7R V. As I said in my review of the latter, with the very high resolution and the lack of an anti-aliasing filter, only Hasselblad and Fuji&#39;s 100-megapixel medium format cameras offer greater detail. It also offers Sony&#39;s Pixel Shift Multi-Shot that can quadruple resolution to 240.8 megapixels. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/78dc69a0-470a-11ee-9de5-bb8002c912aa" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/78dc69a0-470a-11ee-9de5-bb8002c912aa" style="height:1457px;width:2200px;" alt="索尼 A7C 系列推出续集和新 61 兆像素版本" data-uuid="3d8506b7-0786-3ae8-a185-a5b5a2daec27"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sony</div></figure><p> The A7C R can&#39;t shoot 8K video like the A7R V, likely due to heating issues with the smaller body. However, it still offers 4K 60p full-frame video (with pixel binning) and 6.2K oversampled 1.5x cropped 4K 60p video. It comes with S-Log3, S-Cinetone and S-gamut3 Cine, records 10-bit 4:2:2 sampled video and can shoot at up to 120 fps in 1080p mode. Data rates top out at 600Mbps in XAVC SI 4K mode, but you&#39;ll need a (pricey) V90 SD card to shoot that.</p><p> That takes us to a very important consideration: the price. The A7C R costs $3,000, or a full $900 less than the A7R V — something that will give many buyers extreme pause. It arrives in fall of 2023. </p><div id="7d63c80e783447028b677499933d382e"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/imjLX_nZbgI?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no"></iframe></div><h3> Sony A7C II</h3><p> As mentioned, the A7C II has the same 33-megapixel sensor and many of the same specs as the A7 IV. In terms of the body and handling, the form factor and weight are identical to the A7C R — so you get the same extra dial, updated grip, improved EVF and other previously-mentioned features. Unlike the A7C R, though, it doesn&#39;t come with the add-on grip extension in the box.</p><p> Shooting speeds are a bit faster at 10 fps in mechanical or electronic shutter mode. By the way, neither the A7C II or A7C R have full mechanical shutters, but use electronic first curtain shutters. This can create bokeh issues when using lenses with very fast apertures, but otherwise isn&#39;t noticeable. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/a3dc9a20-470b-11ee-bfdf-b538e5e3f876" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/a3dc9a20-470b-11ee-bfdf-b538e5e3f876" style="height:1467px;width:2200px;" alt="索尼的两款新 A7C 系列相机以更少的价格提供优质的功能" data-uuid="72b1387e-d576-369c-a89a-db5d87140d85"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sony</div></figure><p> What&#39;s interesting about the A7C II is that autofocus is superior to the A7 IV because it has the same dedicated AI processing unit as the A7C R (and A7R V) that&#39;s missing on the A7 IV. That means you can expect improved subject detection, tracking and other features compared to the A7 IV. When compared to the A7C, though, Sony promises a 40 percent improvement for animal and bird AF tracking, 60 percent for eye AF and 20 percent for auto exposure tracking.</p><p> Again, image quality should be the same as the A7 IV. That latter delivers sharper photos than the A7 III thanks to the extra resolution, but offers superior low-light capability despite the smaller pixels. A downside to the A7 IV is rolling shutter, so expect the same issue on the A7C II. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/bba4b4d0-470b-11ee-afbb-482d035ca986" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/bba4b4d0-470b-11ee-afbb-482d035ca986" style="height:1467px;width:2200px;" alt="索尼的两款新 A7C 系列相机以更少的价格提供优质的功能" data-uuid="f7c229d7-638a-3b4e-b18e-5f919e243dda"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sony</div></figure><p> In terms of video, the A7C II is actually a better option than the A7C R. It offers sharp full-frame 4K 30p video with 7K oversampling, or 4K 60p with a 1.5x crop. You get 10-bit 4:2:2 color sampling with S-Log3 and S-Cinetone, with LUTs available in camera.</p><p> The Sony A7C II is available in silver and black, and <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATR9mtclZxdkIRpyISWX3kOGAKbJAlKEvpohLzp1ApMy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1784818-REG%2Fsony_a7c_ii_mirrorless_camera.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1784818-REG/sony_a7c_ii_mirrorless_camera.html">arrives this fall for $2,200.</a> That price is a significant $300 less than the A7 IV and it&#39;s actually a better camera in some ways — provided the lack of a second card slot doesn&#39;t bother you. </p><div id="8ff791934e184f0db973ae79cfe16d1e"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/W7kWQFA-ZR4?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/sonys-two-new-a7c-series-cameras-offer-premium-features-for-less-money-080542148.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/sonys-two-new-a7c-series-cameras-offer-premium-features-for-less-money-080542148.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 48f88a4a-e400-46a2-8160-f2fc9f2792e2</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 30 Aug 2023 08:05:42 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693398453</ingested><modified> 2023-08-30T12:27:44+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Cameras & Photography]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1150" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7e921810-4730-11ee-af3f-e2aa8bb0fdb7" width="1792"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1150" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7e921810-4730-11ee-af3f-e2aa8bb0fdb7" width="1792"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Sony]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Sony A7C R camera sits on a rocky ledge with blurred buildings in the background.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sony A7C R]]></media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>